23b96729-8a38-4e15-a2e2-2a624b59687c.26426f0b-7621-4e31-b320-d242e894bc3f.description=
Creare un flusso che legga quali file.txt contiene la cartella creata all’Esercizio 4 e scriva in un
file .xls con 2 colonne\: una con il nome del file ed una con il path.

23b96729-8a38-4e15-a2e2-2a624b59687c.2cbd68aa-6bc4-497b-b0f5-68b963b22026.description=Converts a JSON array or a JSON object to a XML document. Inputs\: json - The JSON array or object (in the form of a String). prettyPrint - The flag for formatting the resulted XML. If it is true the result will contain tabs and newline chars. Default value\: true Valid values\: true, false showXmlDeclaration - The flag for showing the xml declaration (). If this is true then rootTagName can't be empty. Default value\: false Valid values\: true, false rootTagName - The XML tag name. If this input is empty you will get a list of XML elements. defaultJsonArrayItemName - Default XML tag name for items in a JSON array if there isn't a pair (array name, array item name) defined in jsonArraysNames and jsonArraysItemNames. Default value\: item jsonArraysNames - The list of array names separated by delimiter. Examples\: f\:properties jsonArraysItemNames - The coresponding list of array item names separated by delimiter. Examples\: f\:property namespacesPrefixes - The list of tag prefixes separated by delimiter. Examples\: f,ui namespacesUris - The coresponding list of namespaces uris separated by delimiter. Examples\: http\://java.sun.com/jsf/core,urn\:x-hp\:2012\:software\:eve\:uibinding delimiter - The list separator. Default value\: , Results\: returnResult - This is the primary output. The resulted XML document or XML elements. returnCode - 0 for success; -1 for failure. Responses\: success - The operation completed as stated in the description. failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully. Examples\: 1. json\={ "name"\:"John", "age"\:100, "retired"\:true, "otherInfo"\:null } and the other values with their default values you wil get John 100 true Null values are not converted to XML elements. 2. json\=[{"key"\:"year", "value"\:2013}, {"key"\:"month", "value"\:"11"}] and the other values with their default values you wil get year 2013 month 11 3. A complex example that uses all the inputs\: prettyPrint\=true showXmlDeclaration\=true rootTagName\=myroot defaultJsonArrayItemName\=myitem, jsonArraysNames\=f\:properties jsonArraysItemNames\=f\:property namespacesPrefixes\=f,ui namespacesUris\=http\://java.sun.com/jsf/core,urn\:x-hp\:2012\:software\:eve\:uibinding delimiter\=, json\= { "@id"\:"Page1", "ui\:position"\: { "x"\:1, "y"\:2 }, "f\:properties"\: [ { "key1"\:"value1" }, { "key2"\:"value2" } ], "details"\: [ { "type"\:"size", "height"\:10, "width"\:10 }, { "type"\:"color", "name"\:"blue" } ] } The the result will be\: 1 2 value1 value2
size 10 10 color blue
23b96729-8a38-4e15-a2e2-2a624b59687c.9856c586-202b-46be-a1f6-b9cdd18cf724.description=
This operation iterates through a list of values. It is not recommended to modify the value of the "list" and "separator" inputs during the iteration process.

Inputs\:
    list - The list to iterate through.
    separator - A delimiter separating the list elements.
Default value\: ‘,’ (comma) 

Results\:
    resultString - The current list element (if the response is "has more").

Responses\:
    has more - Another value was found in the list and it has been returned.
    no more - The iterator has gone through the entire list. This response is returned once per list iteration.  A subsequent call to the List iterator operation restarts the list iteration process.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
   The position of the iterator in the list is tracked by each step's unique identifier. Therefore, you can simultaneously iterate through the same list from multiple steps.
23b96729-8a38-4e15-a2e2-2a624b59687c.9a60cf5d-e853-4f77-bf20-d264fdcfa6d7.description=
Inserts a new name/value property into a JSON object, where the value is a string. This operation forces the value of the name/vale pair to be a string, no matter what data type it actually is. This means that the  input does not need to be wrapped in quotes as any quotes entered in this input will be escaped, ending up in the properties' value. 
The 'Add JSON Property to Object' operation should be used to add values of type other than string, for example\: another object, an array or a number. 

Examples\: 
1)
    Inputs\:
        jsonObject\: {}
        newPropertyName\: test
        newPropertyValue\: test_value
     Result\:
         { "test"\:"test_value"}
2)
    Inputs\:
        jsonObject\: {}
        newPropertyName\: test
        newPropertyValue\: "test_value"
     Result\:
         { "test"\:"\"test_value\""}
3)
    Inputs\:
        jsonObject\: {}
        newPropertyName\: test
        newPropertyValue\: 1
     Result\:
         { "test"\:"1"}
4)
    Inputs\:
        jsonObject\: {}
        newPropertyName\: test
        newPropertyValue\: [1,2,3,4]
     Result\:
         { "test"\:"[1,2,3,4]"}
     Note the value in the name/value pair above is not a JSON Array, but a plain string that looks like one. 

Inputs\:
    jsonObject - String representation of a JSON object. Objects in JSON are a collection of name value pairs, separated by a colon and surrounded with curly brackets {}. The name must be a string value, and the value can be a single string or any valid JSON object or array.
Examples\: {"one"\:1, "two"\:2}, {"one"\:{"a"\:"a","B"\:"B"}, "two"\:"two", "three"\:[1,2,3.4]}
    newPropertyName - The name of the new property to add to the JSON object. 
Examples\: property1, some_property, another property
    newPropertyValue - The value for the new property. This is interpreted as a string, no matter what the contents of the input. 
Examples\: value1, another value

Results\:
    Result - The JSON array with the inserted element.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully. See the message in  for details.
23b96729-8a38-4e15-a2e2-2a624b59687c.c5c79197-7e0e-42c4-a5dd-ed4bcf08729c.description=
Retrieves the cell data with specified row index and column index in an Excel document. 
XLS, XLSX and XLSM formats are supported. 

Inputs\:
    excelFileName - The absolute path to the new Excel document.
Examples\: c\:\temp\test.xls
    worksheetName - The name of Excel worksheet. 
Default value\: Sheet1
    hasHeader - If Yes, then the first row of the document is expected to be the header row. 
Valid values\: yes, no
Default value\: Yes
    firstRowIndex - The index of the first row in the Excel worksheet, including the header row.
Default value\: 0
    rowIndex - A list of row indexes.
Examples\: 1\:3, 10, 15\:20,25
Default Value\: from the index of the first row  to the index of the last row in the Excel worksheet.
    columnIndex - A list of column indexes.
Examples\: 1\:3, 10, 15\:20,25
Default value\: from 0 to the index of the last column in the Excel worksheet.
    rowDelimiter - The delimiter used to separate the rows of the returnResult.
Default value\: | (pipe)
    columnDelimiter - The delimiter used to separate the columns of the returnResult.
Default value\: , (comma)

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. Returns the cell data retrieved from Excel document.
    header - A delimited list of column names of data being returned if hasHeader is set to Yes. 
    rowsCount - The number of the rows returned.
    columnsCount - The number of the columns returned.

Responses\:
    success - The cell data was retrieved successfully.
    failure - Failed to retireve the cell data.

Notes\:
1. All the index inputs are 0 based.
2. Observed that in some Excel worksheet, the first couple of rows are used for title. So added firstRowIndex input.
3. For the indexes in rowIndex input that is less than the first data row index or greater than the last row index in the worksheet, the operation trims those row indexes.
4. For the indexes in columnIndex input that is less than 0 or greater than the last column index in a row, the operation trims those column indexes.
5. The cell data with fraction format shows as double value in returnResult.
